---
// About / Editorial standards (EN). Key for E-E-A-T and AI citations.
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const alternates = { es: "/quienes-somos", en: "/en/about", fr: "/fr/qui-sommes-nous" };
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Calma Society: an independent quiet-luxury magazine about the Mediterranean. Our editorial standards, independence and view of the island."
  locale="en"
  alternates={alternates}
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-prosa px-5 pb-8 pt-12 sm:px-8 sm:pt-16">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-oro">Calma Society</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl text-tinta sm:text-5xl">About us</h1>
    <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-piedra-suave">
      Calma Society is an independent <strong>quiet-luxury</strong> magazine about the
      Mediterranean. We begin with Menorca: its experiences, its people and its beauty,
      told with judgement and in no hurry.
    </p>

    <div class="article-body mt-10">
      <h2>What we do</h2>
      <p>
        We cover the same things other guides do —coves, food, what's on, places to stay—
        but <strong>elevated</strong>: with editorial judgement, carefully chosen experiences
        and a serene, luxurious eye. We don't believe in noise or ostentation; we believe in
        space, time, honest produce and authenticity.
      </p>

      <h2>Our editorial standards</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Independence.</strong> We recommend out of conviction, not commission.</li>
        <li><strong>First-hand.</strong> We write about what we know and have walked.</li>
        <li><strong>Quality over quantity.</strong> One excellent story beats five fillers.</li>
        <li><strong>Clear facts.</strong> Hours, access, dates and prices when they help.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Independence and transparency</h2>
      <p>
        When content is sponsored, <strong>we always say so</strong>, clearly. The reader's
        trust is our main asset, and it is not for sale. Affiliate links, where present,
        never shape our judgement.
      </p>

      <h2>Why Menorca, and what comes next</h2>
      <p>
        Menorca —a UNESCO Biosphere Reserve and, since 2023, a World Heritage Site for its
        Talayotic legacy— is the opposite of mass tourism: calm, natural, authentic. It is
        our first edition. In time, Calma Society will reach other Mediterranean destinations
        in the same spirit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
